該用noun+noun，咩時候用adj+noun呢？有冇啲咩統一標準？定係叫慣咗所以就咁叫？"},"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2019-11-07T13:04:30.000Z","msg":"依我所知好似真係習慣黎的<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/surprise.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/surprise.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><br />\n有冇英文或者語言系大神賜教下？"},{"pid":"28a89cac429bfe8e8283feae783ace2fe78bc2f0","tid":1698347,"uid":32437,"like":2,"dislike":0,"score":2,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2019-11-07T13:08:29.000Z","msg":"你唔好鑽牛角尖啦"},{"pid":"f25356b9f019067fd5ff8fcb3636a9e5152652de","tid":1698347,"uid":300013,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-11-07T13:08:58.000Z","msg":"information management<br />\noperation management<img src=\"/assets/faces/lm2/smile.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"296e3236da4ddae2543dbf87d249d043a0b60e8d","tid":1698347,"uid":259942,"like":2,"dislike":0,"score":2,"quote":{"pid":"6f65e848b720a7d22010500c8d6dcced67e3a35b","tid":1698347,"uid":64694,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"quote":{"pid":"9817bf8b6f6320f0a409124da0d48b381719036a","tid":1698347,"uid":128248,"like":7,"dislike":1,"score":6,"citedBy":2,"replyTime":"2019-11-07T12:31:34.000Z","msg":"即係chemistry teacher唔會叫chemical teacher 咁囉"},"citedBy":4,"replyTime":"2019-11-07T12:40:08.000Z","msg":"唔，咁咩情況應該用noun+noun，咩時候用adj+noun呢？有冇啲咩統一標準？定係叫慣咗所以就咁叫？"},"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-11-07T13:10:27.000Z","msg":"一定要講嘅話都有標準嘅<br />\nNoun同adjective 都可以做一樣叫modifier 嘅東東<br />\nNoun係可以被自己modify（亦可以被adjectives同determiners例如&rdquo;the, any, no, a, an&rdquo; modify）所以就有revision exercise一詞<br />\n<br />\n係revision exercise依個例子入面，我地會稱revision做modifier，exercise做headword<br />\nModifier要有headword先生存到<br />\nHeadword就可以自己一個"},{"pid":"f8d29d66b4a880fbfd8a5bd17924c7a83ea7a8a2","tid":1698347,"uid":133128,"like":11,"dislike":1,"score":10,"quote":{"pid":"c8fde4ce8226797ab73da2703e6c723c6cfaafdd","tid":1698347,"uid":171849,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"quote":{"pid":"6f65e848b720a7d22010500c8d6dcced67e3a35b","tid":1698347,"uid":64694,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"quote":{"pid":"9817bf8b6f6320f0a409124da0d48b381719036a","tid":1698347,"uid":128248,"like":7,"dislike":1,"score":6,"citedBy":2,"replyTime":"2019-11-07T12:31:34.000Z","msg":"即係chemistry teacher唔會叫chemical teacher 咁囉"},"citedBy":4,"replyTime":"2019-11-07T12:40:08.000Z","msg":"唔，咁咩情況應該用noun+noun，咩時候用adj+noun呢？有冇啲咩統一標準？定係叫慣咗所以就咁叫？"},"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2019-11-07T13:04:30.000Z","msg":"依我所知好似真係習慣黎的<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/surprise.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/surprise.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><br />\n有冇英文或者語言系大神賜教下？"},"citedBy":4,"replyTime":"2019-11-07T13:14:08.000Z","msg":"Revision exercise 唔係一個 compound noun. <br />\n<br />\nCompound noun = 兩個字夾埋變做一個名詞 (single noun phrase), 譬如係 earphone, newspaper, 個兩個夾埋嘅字唔一定係名詞可以係動詞 例如係 playground, playgroup, photocopy etc.<br />\n<br />\nRevision exercise 係一個 noun phrase<br />\n<br />\nExercise 係個head noun, 而Revision 係一個修飾 &ldquo;exercise&rdquo; 嘅premodifier<br />\n<br />\nPremodifer係不限個字嘅syntactic cateogory, 所以係無標準可言 <br />\n<br />\n利申: linguistic master, syntax 攞A"},{"pid":"abd57d7d4c4b9ca2e85f1d639914aecee21bc3a6","tid":1698347,"uid":288510,"like":3,"dislike":1,"score":2,"quote":{"pid":"6f65e848b720a7d22010500c8d6dcced67e3a35b","tid":1698347,"uid":64694,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"quote":{"pid":"9817bf8b6f6320f0a409124da0d48b381719036a","tid":1698347,"uid":128248,"like":7,"dislike":1,"score":6,"citedBy":2,"replyTime":"2019-11-07T12:31:34.000Z","msg":"即係chemistry teacher唔會叫chemical teacher 咁囉"},"citedBy":4,"replyTime":"2019-11-07T12:40:08.000Z","msg":"唔，咁咩情況應該用noun+noun，咩時候用adj+noun呢？有冇啲咩統一標準？定係叫慣咗所以就咁叫？"},"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-11-07T13:20:25.000Z","msg":"其實呢個係一個word formation process，語言學上叫compounding。compounding 係指將兩個已有嘅字痴埋一齊，從而創造出一個新嘅字。而呢個字可以係中間有hyphen (e.g. life-threatening) 可以係就咁拼埋一齊（e.g.  football）亦可以分開，就好似上面啲例子咁。形式方面可以係noun+noun (e.g. bookcase), adj + noun (e.g. good looking) or adj + adj (low-paid) <br />\n<br />\n利申：第一次留言，有錯請更正。"},{"pid":"ae16bb130f85bf026794b8baf7dbcdca7b6