句冇乜分別<br />\n你都知中學既英文miss 英文其實都麻麻<br />\n佢地好多時都會有港式英文既影子<br />\n如: raise up your hands<br />\n但係raise 係唔會搭up 的<br />\nraise 本身就有put up 既意思"},{"pid":"5d8631ddbf4fa339c3440f99750f0ea9f30ff8d4","tid":1698347,"uid":46195,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-11-07T14:35:50.000Z","msg":"compound noun都唔識 <img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/banghead.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"192d03fcf6fccea51552d0bc625e22a14f134ecf","tid":1698347,"uid":133128,"like":1,"dislike":0,"score":1,"quote":{"pid":"0a39462e3813d8a8ca84ffb7d273fb283f1a3f9b","tid":1698347,"uid":64694,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"quote":{"pid":"f8d29d66b4a880fbfd8a5bd17924c7a83ea7a8a2","tid":1698347,"uid":133128,"like":11,"dislike":1,"score":10,"quote":{"pid":"c8fde4ce8226797ab73da2703e6c723c6cfaafdd","tid":1698347,"uid":171849,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2019-11-07T13:04:30.000Z","msg":"依我所知好似真係習慣黎的<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/surprise.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/surprise.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><br />\n有冇英文或者語言系大神賜教下？"},"citedBy":4,"replyTime":"2019-11-07T13:14:08.000Z","msg":"Revision exercise 唔係一個 compound noun. <br />\n<br />\nCompound noun = 兩個字夾埋變做一個名詞 (single noun phrase), 譬如係 earphone, newspaper, 個兩個夾埋嘅字唔一定係名詞可以係動詞 例如係 playground, playgroup, photocopy etc.<br />\n<br />\nRevision exercise 係一個 noun phrase<br />\n<br />\nExercise 係個head noun, 而Revision 係一個修飾 &ldquo;exercise&rdquo; 嘅premodifier<br />\n<br />\nPremodifer係不限個字嘅syntactic cateogory, 所以係無標準可言 <br />\n<br />\n利申: linguistic master, syntax 攞A"},"citedBy":2,"replyTime":"2019-11-07T14:18:41.000Z","msg":"<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> 勁，好詳細嘅解釋，有晒原因<br />\n<br />\n另外我重想問吓點解我哋會成日講「do some revisions」而唔直接講「revise」呢？係咪有咩特別原因？"},"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2019-11-07T15:29:04.000Z","msg":"呢個應該係語用 (pragmatics) 同語義 (semantics) 嘅問題<br />\n<br />\n呢兩個concept可以咁解: e.g. 間房好似好凍<br />\nSemantics: 就係字面上咁解<br />\nPragmatics: 字底嘅暗喻 (可能係叫你去關窗/ 攞件衫俾佢/ 開暖爐)<br />\n<br />\n你講個example: &ldquo;Let&rsquo;s do some revision&rdquo; vs &ldquo;Let&rsquo;s revise&rdquo; 可能就係有呢個分別，兩個句字一樣意思但引申嘅含義可能有唔同 (do some revision 強調係個 do 字，即係叫你 &ldquo;做啦仲問!&rdquo;)<br />\n<br />\n&ldquo;I&rsquo;m being paid today.&rdquo; vs &ldquo;I&rsquo;m getting paid today.&rdquo; 係另一個example - &ldquo;get paid&rdquo; 有一種active agent嘅含義，好似 &ldquo;份人工係抵我拎&rdquo; 嘅意思"},{"pid":"e5e007b054fd9c6464b802c33d6ead9eac90679d","tid":1698347,"uid":64694,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"quote":{"pid":"192d03fcf6fccea51552d0bc625e22a14f134ecf","tid":1698347,"uid":133128,"like":1,"dislike":0,"score":1,"quote":{"pid":"0a39462e3813d8a8ca84ffb7d273fb283f1a3f9b","tid":1698347,"uid":64694,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"quote":{"pid":"f8d29d66b4a880fbfd8a5bd17924c7a83ea7a8a2","tid":1698347,"uid":133128,"like":11,"dislike":1,"score":10,"citedBy":4,"replyTime":"2019-11-07T13:14:08.000Z","msg":"Revision exercise 唔係一個 compound noun. <br />\n<br />\nCompound noun = 兩個字夾埋變做一個名詞 (single noun phrase), 譬如係 earphone, newspaper, 個兩個夾埋嘅字唔一定係名詞可以係動詞 例如係 playground, playgroup, photocopy etc.<br />\n<br />\nRevision exercise 係一個 noun phrase<br />\n<br />\nExercise 係個head noun, 而Revision 係一個修飾 &ldquo;exercise&rdquo; 嘅premodifier<br />\n<br />\nPremodifer係不限個字嘅syntactic cateogory, 所以係無標準可言 <br />\n<br />\n利申: linguistic master, syntax 攞A"},"citedBy":2,"replyTime":"2019-11-07T14:18:41.000Z","msg":"<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> 勁，好詳細嘅解釋，有晒原因<br />\n<br />\n另外我重想問吓點解我哋會成日講「do some revisions」而唔直接講「revise」呢？係咪有咩特別原因？"},"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2019-11-07T15:29:04.000Z","msg":"呢個應該係語用 (pragmatics) 同語義 (semantics) 嘅問題<br />\n<br />\n呢兩個concept可以咁解: e.g. 間房好似好凍<br />\nSemantics: 就係字面上咁解<br />\nPragmatics: 字底嘅暗喻 (可能係叫你去關窗/ 攞件衫俾佢/ 開暖爐)<br />\n<br />\n你講個example: &ldquo;Let&rsquo;s do some revision&rdquo; vs &ldquo;Let&rsquo;s revise&rdquo; 可能就係有呢個分別，兩個句字一樣意思但引申嘅含義可能有唔同 (do some revision 強調係個 do 字，即係叫你 &ldquo;做啦仲問!&rdquo;)<br />\n<br />\n&ldquo;I&rsquo;m being paid today.&rdquo; vs &ldquo;I&rsquo;m getting paid today.&rdquo; 係另一個example - &ldquo;get paid&rdquo; 有一種active agent嘅含義，好似 &ldquo;份人工係抵我拎&rdquo; 嘅意思"},"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2019-11-07T16:36:37.000Z","msg":"哦，即係有啲係客觀描述緊件事，有啲係有少少主觀再另加自己少少嘅情感落去，有語氣上嘅分別，例如上面do some revision係有加強強調嘅意味，俾你咁講一講，我突然諗起有一句成日講嘅都係咁，&quot;I do remember&quot;同&quot;I remember&quot;<br />\n<br />\n有啲係active主動，有啲係passive被動描述<br />\n<br />\n有少少明白你嘅意思"},{"pid":"135b9bb755d1b56b81e7e8f102ad039207b54fae","tid":1698347,"uid":64694,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-11-07T16:47:03.000Z","msg":"上面有巴打話noun phrase，我搵到一個幾好嘅網講呢樣嘢，佢有一個幾好嘅例子，佢個例子嘅structure好清楚<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/agree.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><br />\n<br />\n<a href=\"https://www.teachingenglish.org.uk/article/noun-phrase\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.teachingenglish.org.uk%2Farticle%2Fnoun-phrase&d=Z9XWEpuBYzNDjlwSEAyqKzQSOVv8pHkqsyXWJi2kweQ%3D&h=96032abc\" data-auto-link target=\"_blank\">https://www.teachingenglish.org.uk/article/noun-phrase</a>"},{"pid":"2ed755ae31ba3f82255437fa5733239ceda561d3","tid":1698347,"uid":133128,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"quote":{"pid":"e5e007b054fd9c6464b802c33d6ead9eac90679d","tid":1698347,"uid":64694,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"quote":{"pid":"192d03fcf6fccea51552d0bc625e22a14f134ecf","tid":1698347,"uid":133128,"like":1,"dislike":0,"score":1,"quote":{"pid":"0a39462e3813d8a8ca84ffb7d273fb283f1a3f9b","tid":1698347,"uid":64694,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":2,"replyTime":"2019-11-07T14:18:41.000Z","msg":"<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/adore.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /> 勁，好詳細嘅解釋，有晒原因<br />\n<br />\n另外我重想問吓點解我哋會成日講「do some revisions」而唔直接講「revise」呢？係咪有咩特別原因？"},"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2019-11-07T15:29:04.000Z","msg":"呢個應該係語用 (pragmatics) 同語義 (semantics) 嘅問題<br />\n<br />\n呢兩個concept可以咁解: e.g. 間房好似好凍<br />\nSemantics: 就係字面上咁解<br />\nPragmatics: 字底嘅暗喻 (可能係叫你去關窗/ 攞件衫俾佢/ 開暖爐)<br />\n<br />\n你講個example: &ldquo;Let&rsquo;s do some revision&rdquo; vs &ldquo;Let&rsquo;s revise&rdquo; 可能就係有呢個分別，兩個句字一樣意思但引申嘅含義可能有唔同 (do some revision 強調係個 do 字，即係叫你 &ldquo;做啦仲問!&rdquo;)<br />\n<br />\n&ldquo;I&rsquo;m being paid today.&rdquo; vs &ldquo;I&rsquo;m getting paid today.&rdquo; 係另一個example - &ldquo;get paid&rdquo; 有一種active agent嘅含義，好似 &ldquo;份人工係抵我拎&rdquo; 嘅意思"},"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2019-11-07T16:36:37.000Z","msg":"哦，即係有啲係客觀描述緊件事，有啲係有少少主觀再另加自己少少嘅情感落去，有語氣上嘅分別，例如上面do some revision係有加強強調嘅意味，俾你咁講一講，我突然諗起有一句成日講嘅都係咁，&quot;I do remember&quot;同&quot;I remember&quot;<br />\n<br />\n有啲係active主動，有啲係passive被動描述<br />\n<br />\n有少少明白你嘅意思"},"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-11-07T17:17:24.000Z","msg":"Errr 如果要分析嘅話，就只可以講字面上同暗喻嘅意思，同主觀客觀係冇關係<br />\n<br />\n同埋你個 &ldquo;do&rdquo; example同我個 &ldquo;do&rdquo; 係唔可以相提並論:<br />\n<br />\n&rdquo;I do remember&rdquo; (個do係助動詞，本身就有強調語氣嘅語義，但係冇主唔主動嘅分別)<br />\n<br />\n&ldquo;Let&rsquo;s do some revision&rdquo; (個do係主動詞，本身係冇!!! 強調語氣嘅分支義，但係有字面上主動&rdquo;做&rdquo; 嘅意思)<br />\n<br />\n(留意番!! 我係借朋友ac留言!!!)"},{"pid":"721e0f3a3cea3d361c6e670b4b8b55ab14e62a97","tid":1698347,"uid":160554,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-11-07T17:19:42.000Z","msg":"屌好心啦"},{"pid":"28d5d998a8f55b945e4ef56f3f43d7056561ac28","tid":1698347,"uid":303982,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"quote":{"pid":"6f65e848b720a7d22010500c8d6dcced67e3a35b","tid":1698347,"uid":64694,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"quote":{"pid":"9817bf8b6f6320f0a409124da0d48b381719036a","tid":1698347,"uid":128248,"like":7,"dislike":1,"score":6,"citedBy":2,"replyTime":"2019-11-07T12:31:34.000Z","msg":"即係chemistry teacher唔會叫chemical teacher 咁囉"},"citedBy":4,"replyTime":"2019-11-07T12:40:08.000Z","msg":"唔，咁咩情況應該用noun+noun，咩時候用adj+noun呢？有冇啲咩統一標準？定係叫慣咗所以就咁叫？"},"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-11-07T17:36:52.000Z","msg":"冇規則，係語意<br />\nchemical 係化學物<br />\nchemistry 係化學"},{"pid":"7f75cc56ea182c94c0452267880b380519ee817f","tid":1698347,"uid":97887,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"quote":{"pid":"f8d29d66b4a880fbfd8a5bd17924c7a83ea7a8a2","tid":1698347,"uid":133128,"like":11,"dislike":1,"score":10,"quote":{"pid":"c8fde4ce8226797ab73da2703e6c723c6cfaafdd","tid":1698347,"uid":171849,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"quote":{"pid":"6f65e848b720a7d22010500c8d6dcced67e3a35b","tid":1698347,"uid":64694,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":4,"replyTime":"2019-11-07T12:40:08.000Z","msg":"唔，咁咩情況應該用noun+noun，咩時候用adj+noun呢？有冇啲咩統一標準？定係叫慣咗所以就咁叫？"},"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2019-11-07T13:04:30.000Z","msg":"依我所知好似真係習慣黎的<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/surprise.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/surprise.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" /><br />\n有冇英文或者語言系大神賜教下？"},"citedBy":4,"replyTime":"2019-11-07T13:14:08.000Z","msg":"Revision exercise 唔係一個 compound noun. <br />\n<br />\nCompound noun = 兩個字夾埋變做一個名詞 (single noun phrase), 譬如係 earphone, newspaper, 個兩個夾埋嘅字唔一定係名詞可以係動詞 例如係 playground, playgroup, photocopy etc.<br />\n<br />\nRevision exercise 係一個 noun phrase<br />\n<br />\nExercise 係個head noun, 而Revision 係一個修飾 &ldquo;exercise&rdquo; 嘅premodifier<br />\n<br />\nPremodifer係不限個字嘅syntactic cateogory, 所以係無標準可言 <br />\n<br />\n利申: linguistic master, syntax 攞A"},"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-11-07T23:17:33.000Z","msg":"A compound noun is a noun phrase made up of two nouns, e.g. bus driver, in which the first noun acts as a sort of adjective for the second one, but without really describing it."},{"pid":"4ac732645d4152f0750929e1dbab7698f32f9f34","tid":1698347,"uid":143909,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-11-07T23:32:57.000Z","msg":"premodifier分classfier同describer<br />\n<br />\ndescriber一定係adjective, e.g. beautiful girl個beautiful<br />\n<br />\nclassifier通常係講緊總類,revision exercise係講緊特別一種專要黎做revision既exercise,上面driver又係taxi driver同bus driver就係講緊某一種類既driver"},{"pid":"8ab4d804dc258ef6cf3c81c835c3799887a61229","tid":1698347,"uid":263086,"like":0,"dislike":1,"score":-1,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-11-07T23:33:30.000Z","msg":"&quot;Bus stop&quot;<br />\n此post已完"},{"pid":"c5995a0f8bf42db4b9cf7e48b